<h1>Climbing Permissions</h1>

<p>Climbing adventures are a special case because they are very dangerous.  You
can be an excellent climber and still not be able to <b>lead</b> an <b>official
club adventure</b> for climbing.  You must be approved by the officers to do
this; you are welcome to climb with your friends, and even use the club mailing
list to announce it, but an official club climbing adventure is a completely
different matter.  Please see also the <a
href="members/resources/trip-climb">climbing checklist</a>.</p>

<h2>Authorized Leaders</h2>

<p>The following people are allowed to lead the following types of
adventures:</p>

<ol>
<li>Aarash Sofla is allowed to lead all climbing activities</li>
<li>Thiago Ize is allowed to lead all rock climbing activities</li>
</ol>

<p>Top rope</p>

<ol>
<li>Bruce Spottiswoode</li>
</ol>

<p>Sport</p>

<ol>
<li>Sophie Johnson</li>
<li>Bruce Spottiswoode</li>
<li>Matt Oberhart</li>
<li>Ryan Pevnick</li>
</ol>

<p>Trad</p>

<ol>
<li>Nobody else</li>
</ol>

<h2>Borrowing Gear for Personal Use:</h2>

<p>To protect the equipment, and those who will use it afterwards, we don't
allow everyone to borrow climbing gear.  The following people are allowed to
borrow gear for personal use:</p>

<p>Top rope</p>

<ol>
<li>Sophie Johnson</li>
<li>Bruce Spottiswoode</li>
<li>Matt Oberhart</li>
</ol>

<p>Sport</p>

<ol>
<li>Sophie Johnson</li>
